REVENUE RECOGNITION 
Revenue is recognized when the firm has: 
¶  Performed all, or a substantial portion of, the services to be provided 
¶  Incurred a substantial majority of the costs, and the remaining costs can be estimated 
¶  Received either cash, a receivable, or some other asset for which 
A reasonable precise value can be measured 
• 
•  Collectibility can be assured 

 
 

