INVENTORY (LIFO VS. FIFO) 
¶  LIFO and FIFO produce temporary differences in accounting numbers   
¶  No approach is superior 
¶  Firms using LIFO will give information to make numbers comparable across firms1 
¶  Relevant formulae 
LIFO Reserve = cumulative difference in FIFO – LIFO inventory 
• 
LIFO Reserve = Ending InvFIFO – Ending InvLIFO 
• 
Change in LIFO Reserve = COGSLIFO – COGSFIFO 
• 
INVEB = INVBB + P2 – COGS 
• 
¶  Make sure you know when to use the absolute amount in the LIFO Reserve and when to use 
changes in the LIFO Reserve 

