¶  Three key ways to depreciate a fixed asset: 
1)  Straight-line Depreciation Method 
2)  Production (Depletion) Method 
3)  Accelerated Depreciation 
¶  Four simple steps to depreciation: 
1)  Assess total cost to be allocated over time 
2)  Estimate the salvage value (all methods except for double-declining balance) 
3)  Estimate useful life 
4)  Choose depreciation method 
¶  Watch the sign convention for Accumulated Depreciation! 

